defaultI 
defaultam grateful to you for giving me the opportunity to contribute to your committee's 
defaultinquiries into complaints handling.
defaultBefore addressing the specific questions posed in your letter, I think it would be 
defaulthelpful to the work of your committee if I sketched ou
defaultt some background information 
defaulton the Housing Ombudsman.
defaultBackground to the Housing Ombudsman Service defaultJurisdiction:defaultThe statutory Housing Ombudsman was created by the Housing Act 1996 and 
defaultcommenced operating as such on 1 April 1997. The relevant provisions of the1996 Act were amended in the Housing and Regeneration Act of 2008 and, more 
defaultsignificantly, in the Localism Act of 2011. The Housing Ombudsman is a corporation 
defaultsole and operates unde
defaultr a Scheme approved by the Secretary of State (of the 
defaultDCLG).
defaultI defaultam the second statutory Housing Ombudsman and was appointed in 2001. Until 1 
defaultApril 2013 my jurisdiction covered private not-for-profit (or 'not-for-dividend') 
defaultlandlords who are required by the 
default1996 Act to be members of my Scheme "for all his 
defaulthousing activities" and private for-profit landlords and managing agents who may 
defaultchose to be members. Since 1 April 2013 all the retained stock owned or managed 
defaultby Local Housing Authorities (LHAs) or by Arms
default Length Management Organisations 
default(ALMOs) on their behalf has come within my jurisdiction. Leaseholders of all 
defaultmember landlords are protected by my Scheme; there are, for example, about 
default300,000 leaseholders of LHAs and they, like leaseholders in the 'housin
defaultg 
defaultassociation' sector, do not fall into the definition of 'social housing' in the 2008 Act.
defaultSince 1 April 2013, therefore, it would be possible to categorise the Housing 
defaultOmbudsman Service as a 'hybrid', having jurisdiction in both the private and public
default 
defaultsectors. This is captured in our mission statement which is "impartial dispute 
defaultresolution in rented housing".
defaultThere are now 5.1 million units and about 12.5 million people in my jurisdiction. My Service is funded by the private, for-profit and not-for-profit, landlords who pay £1.47 
defaultper unit per annum and grant-in-aid from government of £847,000 for the LHA 
defaultdimens
defaultion of my jurisdiction.
defaultLocalism act 2011:defaultThe Secretary of State chose my Service to be the single housing ombudsman in the 
defaultLocalism Act so that there would be a "common route of redress for housing tenants" and "consistency in the treatment of complaints
default".
defaultIn 2011, the impact assessment which preceded the Bill stated that government policy was to:
default"...provide a common route of redress for all complaints about the performance of social housing landlords by designating a single, specialist 
defaultombudsman for soc
defaultial housing. In April 2010 a new cross-domain regulatory system was brought into effect, ensuring that tenants of local authorities and 
defaulthousing associations can expect a broadly similar level of service from their 
defaultlandlord. Given the move 
defaultto consistent standards across social housing, we 
defaultnow wish to put complaint handling on a more consistent footing 
defaultby
defaultdesignating
default a single ombudsman for all complaints about social housing 
defaultlandlords. At the same time, we want to ensure that there continues 
defaultto be 
defaulta
defaulthigh
default quality ombudsman service for all social housing tenants and their 
defaultrepresentatives"
defaultDesignating my Service as the single housing ombudsman was the preferred option because of our "existing single focus on housing". The option of giving the ext
defaultended 
defaultjurisdiction to the Local Government Ombudsmen was rejected as that would not 
defaulthave resulted in there being a single ombudsman "specialising" in complaints about 
defaultlandlords as their remit covers all Local Government services. This was consistent 
defaultwith g
defaultovernment's intention to have a single ombudsman in the context of a single, 
defaultcross-domain regulator where there were "common standards set by a single regulator" and where it would make little sense for complaints about landlord performance (including agai
defaultnst the standards) to be considered by two different ombudsmen.
defaultThese changes in the Localism Act stemmed from the government's recent review of social housing regulation which concluded, among other things, that the system for 
defaultmanaging social housing comp
defaultlaints should be changed in order to strengthen the 
defaultrole of locally elected representatives and tenant groups, and address a perceived democratic deficit in understanding of housing issues at the local level. The review 
defaultrecommended that a 'democratic filter' should be introduced so that in future tenants 
defaultwho had exhausted their landlord's complaints procedure would have to go through their local tenant panel, MP, or councillor, who, in turn, would seek to resolve the 
defaultcomp
defaultlaint before, if needed, referring the issue to the Ombudsman.
default&#xa0;
defaultIf there had not been changes to the Bill as it passed through the House of Lords 
defaultcomplaints would only have reached me if one of these 'designated persons' had referred it on to me. If they had not, the grievance would have died where it stood 
defaultand complainants would have been barred from bringing the issue to me. Their only, and remote
default, opportunity for redress would have been through the ballot box.
defaultChanges in the Lords resulted in residents being given a much wider range of 
defaultchoices in terms of seeking resolution of their grievances if not satisfied at the 
defaultconclusion of their landlords'
default internal complaints procedures (ICPs).
defaultDirect access to the Housing Ombudsman:defaultIn spite of clear provision to the contrary in the Localism Act, a myth has grown up 
defaultthat disputes cannot come to me until eight weeks have passed after completion of 
defaultproviders
default' internal complaints procedures (ICPs). This is a misunderstanding of the 
defaultAct and of my Scheme approved by the Secretary of State.
defaultIt is true that one choice would be to wait eight weeks and come straight to me but 
defaultresidents 
defaultmight decide instead to go to 
defaulta designated person (any MP, a local 
defaultcouncillor, or a designated tenant panel) and ask them to resolve the dispute. What is less commonly understood is that they may go to a designated person and ask 
defaultthem to refer their dispute to me immediately. The desig
defaultnated person may agree to 
defaultor reject the request but, provided that agreement or rejection is in writing or 
defaultconfirmed in writing, the matter could be with me the same day.
defaultThis means that all tenants of councils and of private, not-for-profit landlords may 
defaultuse the designated persons to achieve not only the 'dual track' access to me that was recommended by the Law Commission but also resolution of disputes by designated persons themselves. The choice lies with tenants depending on their 
defaultneeds and the outcomes
default they are seeking. Their landlords are best placed to help them make the right choice.
defaultTenants of those for-profit landlords who have chosen to join my Scheme can still 
defaultbring their disputes to me without having to decide whether or not to engage with 
defaultdesig
defaultnated persons.
defaultThe crucial upshot of these provisions is, of course, that all residents and tenants in 
defaultmy jurisdiction may have immediate and direct access to my Service if they so wish.
defaultLocal dispute resolution:defaultWe have made changes to ensure that more resources are devoted to early, local resolution where that is appropriate and proportionate. One example of this is that I 
defaultnow have the power, at any time, to promote local resolution of a dispute between 
defaultany landl
defaultord and any tenant in my jurisdiction by either referring the complaint back to the complainant and provider (and/or a designated person) or by providing them 
defaultwith assistance to resolve the dispute. Also, I may decide to suspend or not to 
defaultprogress an inves
defaulttigation if I think there is opportunity to resolve the dispute locally. 
defaultSo, for instance, if a complainant refers a matter to me before completing an ICP, my
default 
defaultnew power enables me to offer a solution to the parties there and then. Equa
defaultlly, I 
defaultmay propose a form of local resolution in any of the circumstances described above.
defaultStrategy reviews:defaultIn 2006 we carried out a fundamental review of our core process and people development practices. In consequence, performance against targets for the 
defaultorganisation improved yearly. The work that was then required to prepare for my 
defaultextended jurisdiction amou
defaultnted to the most far-reaching review of the Service since 
defaultit came into being on 1 April 1997.
defaultIn order to support Parliament's intention that, where possible, complaints should be 
defaultdealt with simply and quickly at local level and that an effective service i
defaults provided to 
defaultthose cases which are escalated to me we executed an ambitious change 
defaultprogramme which linked into our strategic imperatives. We carried out a fundamental 
defaultreview of all aspects of the organisation with one of our most important priorities 
defaultbein
defaultg to re-align resources to focus on front-end delivery.
defaultOur strategic aims for 2012-13 were delivered by means of a Transition Plan that 
defaultidentified and mapped specific, timed objectives and work-streams that:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
