defaultHousing Ombudsman'sdefault new role:defaultMy new, two-pronged, role is now stated succinctly in the introduction to my new 
defaultScheme that was approved by the Secretary of State in February 2013; it is to 
defaultresolve disputes involving members of the Scheme, including making awards of 
defaultcompensat
defaultion or other remedies when appropriate, as well as to support effective 
defaultlandlord-tenant dispute resolution by others. This new, composite role is now 
defaultreflected in the changes to our strategic outcomes, revisions to the Scheme which 
defaultregulates the Service, t
defaulthe re-engineered core process, new Dispute Resolution 
defaultPrinciples, new learning media, and a re-focussed stakeholder management 
defaultstrategy.
defaultThe first 'prong' of my role is clearly reflected in our mission statement (above). We 
defaultaim to provide an escalated comp
defaultlaint-handling and dispute-resolution service which 
defaultis trusted, valued, and respected because it is fair, independent, impartial (free of 
defaultbias and prejudice), effective, efficient, transparent, appropriate, proportionate, and 
defaultrelevant. Equally, we aim to p
defaultrovide or assist dispute resolution, especially locally, 
defaultwherever possible and this theme is picked up in our vision which is to "work with 
defaultothers to increase trust in dispute resolution and to improve landlord and tenant 
defaultrelations".
defaultThe primary outcomes o
defaultf our vision and mission are that, in 2016:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTenants and landlords have increased trust in dispute resolution;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTenant and landlord relations are improved;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLandlords have a positive view of complaints;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDesignated persons are playing their part in resolving 
defaultdisputes fairly.
defaultPhilosophy:defaultThe changes to my jurisdiction and role as from April 2013 required a consequential 
defaultrevision to our philosophy which is now as follows:
default"In essence, we provide a high quality, impartial service to people who live in, 
defaultsupply, or manage housing. We offer our experience, skills, expertise, and guidance to help tenants, landlords, MPs, councillors, and tenant panels. We
defaultare not regulators. We are conciliators and problem-solvers. We provide objective solutions at the earli
defaultest appropriate point. We make a positive 
defaultcontribution to the quality of housing and dispute resolution within the Ombudsman's jurisdiction by:
defaulta) enabling and encouraging landlords to improve their standards of housing
defaultmanagement through our independent, 
defaultimpartial, and objective role by:
default- explaining the advantages of complying with our determinations, and 
default- encouraging a positive attitude to the value of the outcomes of complaints and similar feedback
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaulthelping to improve tenants' individual and shared amenity, environment, 
defaultand quality of life
defaultc)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultsharing our expertise, principles, and lessons learnt by highlighting 
defaultinstances of good practice revealed by our process, and
defaultd)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultsupporting good landlord and tenant re
defaultlations."
defaultOverall strategic intent:defaultBy achieving our mission, vision, their primary outcomes, and our philosophy we 
defaultshall realise our overall strategic intent which is to be relevant, make an impact, 
defaultmake a difference, and add value by:
defaulta)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBeing a catalyst for change in the rented-housing sector having fundamentally 
defaultre-engineered, once again, our dispute resolution process with particular 
defaultemphasis on the customer's perspective;
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBeing the champion of good practice and the source of excellence
default in 
defaultcomplaint handling and dispute resolution in rented housing through 
defaultappropriate and proportionate methods of dissemination;
defaultc)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDemonstrating that we are making an impact by collecting more data that 
defaultprovide evidence of the success of the measures we shall
default set for 
defaultorganisational performance, service delivery, and monitoring improvement in 
defaultdispute resolution practice in the sector;
defaultd)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultApplying our resources proportionately to the ombudsman functions of 
defaultinvestigation, systemic failures, and knowledge disseminati
defaulton.
defaultDeveloping, improving, and enhancing the following nine characteristics of the value 
defaultadded by our service delivery will make a significant contribution to the success of 
defaultour strategy:
defaulti)
default              
defaultWe help improve customer service and positive relationships:
defaultThe outputs of our investigations where service failure or maladministration is found 
defaultare in the form of recommendations or orders, or both. They may require providers 
defaultto:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTell us how they propose to put right the failings we have identified;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGive, or rest
defaultore to, residents their entitlements under statute or contract;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIntroduce, amend, or properly apply their policies;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMake an apology;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPay compensation.
defaultWhether or not we find maladministration our principal aims in composing decisions 
defaultare to:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPut residents into the position in which they should have been but for their 
defaultprovider's failure;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnable providers to learn from our findings and apply that learning to the 
defaultimprovement of the quality of the service they provide;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHelp 
defaultimprove or sustain a positive relationship between providers and residents;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultContribute to the improvement of customer service.
defaultii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProviders comply with our recommendations and orders:
defaultThere have been very few instances since 1997 in which providers have faile
defaultd to 
defaultcomply with my recommendations or orders. They recognise, as the Law 
defaultCommission put it (in their Consultation Paper 196 ) the "political or moral pressure" 
defaulton them to put things right following a decision of the Ombudsman. They are also confident that
default the Ombudsman is independent and operates an impartial, quality-
defaultmanaged process that draws conclusions only from careful analysis of available evidence.
defaultiii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe provide advice, assistance, and signposting:
defaultEven before 1 April 2013 and the re-configuration of our core process to concentrate 
defaultresources on early dispute resolution, about 90% of cases were already being closed 
defaultwithout investigation.
