defaultWe give an external perspective:
defaultOften, we 'shine a light' into areas that are obscured from the view of providers. 
defaultUsually, they accept our findings, acknowledge their failings, and put them right. Even when they may be displeased by the discovery that their systems or 
defaultmanagement procedures are not as good as they thought they were providers still 
defaulttend to accept our de
defaultcisions recognising that they are fair and un-biased and that the 
defaultOmbudsman has a unique perspective on the way their organisations operate in 
defaultpractice.
