defaultWe make 
default'gratis' 
defaultrecommendations:
defaultEven where we do not make a finding of service failure or maladminist
defaultration we 
defaultsometimes make suggestions to providers for them to consider as part of their customer care and service provision. How they deal with those suggestions is a 
defaultmatter for them but we consider this to be another contribution to the value that we 
defaultcan 
defaultadd to providers and their residents to enrich service provision and customer 
defaultcare.
defaultvi)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe identify service failure:
defaultFrom April 2013 and the operation of the new Scheme, I have been able to make 
defaultfindings not only of maladministration but also service failure. A finding of 
defaultmaladministration or, indeed, severe maladministration will still be available to and 
defaultwill be made in appropriate circumstances but extending the spectrum of 
defaultmaladministration wi
defaultll 
defaultenable findings that would not have merited the strength of 
defaultcriticism evoked by the concept of 'maladministration'. Feedback we have received 
defaultfrom providers and other 
defaultstakeholders indicates that providers are more likely to 
defaultreact with good grace to, and
default residents will, accordingly, benefit from, such findings 
defaultwhich can be expressed in more conciliatory and positive terms.
defaultvii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe encourage local solutions:
defaultI now have the power to authorise the drafting of many more orders and 
defaultrecommendations in terms that wil
defaultl set out the presenting issues and then require 
defaultproviders to design appropriate remedial actions. Again, feedback from providers 
defaultand other stakeholders during the consultation process that preceded formal 
defaultapproval of my new Scheme, indicated that provider
defaults would more likely to be 
defaultencouraged to take responsibility for resolving disputes and be more likely to 
defaultproduce an outcome that suits local conditions and meets the particular needs of residents especially if providers work with tenant scrutiny panels. We
default are gathering 
defaultdata against which we shall test these assumptions.
defaultviii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUnder the terms of my Scheme, providers are expected to comply with my 
defaultdeterminations. If they do not, I have the power to:
defaulta)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultRequire them to report to me on compliance with a determination in such a 
defaultway and at such a time as I may specify;
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultReport them to any appropriate regulatory agency and/or, in accordance with 
defaultthe policy o
defaultf localism and co-regulation as expressed in the Localism Act, the 
defaultboards, committees, or tenant scrutiny panels of providers;
defaultc)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOrder them to publish that they have failed to comply, in such a way as I see fit;
defaultd)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPublish the facts and circumstances of non-compliance naming the providers 
defaultin my annual report or elsewhere.
defaultix)
default              
defaultWe share our learning:
defaultAn important objective of my Service has always been to share lessons learnt not 
defaultonly with landlords but also with other
defaults with an interest in the outcomes of our core 
defaultprocess. Traditionally, we have done this by publishing reports, speaking at 
defaultconferences and seminars, and providing training for Board members, front-line staff, and tenants. Landlords, in particular, have fe
defaultd back to us that these initiatives have 
defaulthelped them to change and to design policies and practices in respect of complaint-
defaulthandling in particular and wider customer service in general. Our historical shared-
defaultlearning 
defaultinter-actions with providers and residents were so well-valued and 
defaultrespected that we were frequently approached by landlords and landlord and tenant 
defaultbodies to deliver it for them by special request.
defaultTo deliver our current vision and mission we intend to wo
defaultrk with landlords and 
defaulttenants to resolve disputes that come to us impartially using processes that are fair, 
defaultevidence-based, and free of bias and prejudice. These principles of dispute 
defaultresolution will be,the basis of 
defaultour work with landlords, tenants, MPs, 
defaultcouncillors, and 
defaulttenant panels. We are developing an extended set of dispute resolution principles 
defaultwhich will be augmented by complementary learning media. Working with all 
defaultinterested parties, we aim to achieve accessible dispute resolution that will be of
default 
defaultbenefit to both landlords and tenants and encourage landlords to use these 
defaultoutcomes to improve the services they provide.
defaultGovernance:defaultThe Housing Act 1996 (Sch. 2., para.10) provides for the Ombudsman's Scheme to 
defaultbe administered by a body corporate or by 
defaulta corporation sole. Until 1 April 2013 
defaultthere was a body corporate, IHO Limited, a company limited by guarantee and not 
defaulttrading for profit which, in 2006, was designated as an eNDPB. The Board 
defaultcomprised equal numbers of tenants, landlords, and independents 
default(the 'constituency 
defaultmodel'). The Secretary of State made an order establishing The Housing 
defaultOmbudsman as a corporation sole. As Ombudsman, Chief Executive, and
default 
defaultAccounting Officer, I am supported
default by an Audit and Risk Committee. In accordance 
defaultwith an express provision in the Scheme I may set up a Panel of Advisors but such a 
defaultgroup is not part of the governance of the corporation sole and advises me 
defaultpersonally.
defaultThe principal reasons for changes in g
defaultovernance were:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo support my independence as Ombudsman in the discharge of my 
defaultstatutory function;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo remove 'double governance';
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo reduce the costs (direct and indirect) of servicing two full governance 
defaultstructures;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo remove the potential for conflict 
defaultarising from my three roles;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe extension of jurisdiction under the Localism Act 2011;
default
